{
  "text": "The bulk of the literature on the insurance-growth nexus theory focuses on analysis of a few nations over a various times [e.g. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Only limited scholarly attention has been devoted to the insurance sector in transition economies, and there are only a few econometric works on the interaction between the insurance sector expansion and economic growth in those countries, which have now completed their initial transition stage. It is important to better understand this relationship in those economies because insurance industry development is a core regulatory and policy issue that may meaningfully impact growth.",
  "correct_citation": {
